metadata.name: FXHASH Generative Logo #191
metadata.description:
Unique iteration of the first Generative Token minted on fxhash.

It also servers as the actual logo of the platform. It represents the generative processes driving fxhash tokens. Generative Tokens are fed with a unique hash to produce unique outputs based on the hash — they are functions with a hash as single input.

The growth that comes out of the text is driven by a "Dividing-Aggregating Walkers" (DAW) algorithm. The hash drives all the DAW settings, as well as a mutation factor which is responsible for changes in each Walker parameters as they divide.

Some iterations will produce very simple outputs whereas others might be more chaotic.

Piece by @ciphrd for fxhash

metadata.name: Cubick 2.0 #38
metadata.description:
Each output is generated by layering Blender renders.

Each output is formed from 4 "squares". These squares can be at different angles to each other, but occasionally, the squares line up to form a "cube". Statistically, about 1 in 30 outputs are likely to be a cube. Will you mint a cube?

The color of the middle two squares can vary, whereas the outer squares are always cream in color.

The variations are best viewed in live mode.

All outputs in this collection will have the same color palette (called Vintage).

In live mode:
Click/tap the image to make a "Download image" button appear. Click this button to download a 1000x1000px PNG.

metadata.name: Cometary coma #108
metadata.description:
Made of ice and comet dust.
Nebulous envelope surrounding the nucleus of a comet.
Formed when passing close to the Sun on its highly elliptical orbit.

As the comet warms, parts of it sublimate.
